-- Mangalore Refinery Buys Oman, Qua Iboe Oil From Itochu, Glencore
-- B y   P r a t i s h   N a r a y a n a n
-- 2012-08-28T05:58:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-28/mangalore-refinery-buys-oman-qua-iboe-oil-from-itochu-glencore.html
Mangalore Refinery & Petrochemicals
Ltd. (MRPL)  bought crude for loading in October, according to three
traders with knowledge of the purchases.  The company bought 600,000 barrels of Oman crude, a high-
sulfur grade of oil, from  Itochu Corp. (8001)  at a premium of $2.50 a
barrel to Dubai prices, the traders said, asking not to be named
because the information is confidential.  Mangalore bought Qua Iboe, a low-sulfur crude, from
 Glencore International Plc (GLEN)  at a premium of $5.70 a barrel to
Dated Brent prices, they said.  Details of the purchases follow:  To contact the reporter on this story:
